# Mimir

Use Mimir for durable repo memory when available.

Mimir is memory only, not approval authority.

Use Mimir for recall, search, durable decisions, blocker continuity, and session outcome recording.

At task start, use `memory_recall` / `memory_search` when relevant before duplicating work.

At completion for meaningful work, run:

```text
commit chat history to Mimir MCP memory
```

Operational meaning: call `memory_record_outcome` and store concise session outcome, not raw chat history. Include task, changed files, verification, Aion session id if any, final status, blockers, and next step.

Use `yes` only if the tool succeeds. Use `BLOCKED (<reason>)` if Mimir is unavailable or the write fails.

Never store secrets, credentials, `.env`, API keys, raw dumps, full files, private user data, or noisy temporary details.

If Mimir is blocked, use `project_knowledge.md` / `project_history.md` only when this repo has that fallback convention.

Details: `docs/mimir-tools.md`, `.cursor/skills/mimir/SKILL.md`
